      "content": "The feeling that resistance is pointless when confronting an infinite void is deeply isolating and exhausting. Wanting to cease the struggle when the ultimate outcome feels meaningless is a sign of immense emotional pain. Please remember that even when the universe seems indifferent, your immediate, felt experience of this moment is real and valuable to you. If the idea of stopping feels tempting, speaking to a professional who understands existential distress can offer new ways to navigate those feelings.",
